# Practical 9 — Data Visualization II

# MAIN TOPICS

* Boxplot
* Quartiles
* Outliers

---

# IMPORTANT THEORY

# Boxplot

Statistical graph showing:

* median
* quartiles
* spread
* outliers

---

# Quartiles

| Quartile | Meaning |
| -------- | ------- |
| Q1       | 25%     |
| Q2       | median  |
| Q3       | 75%     |

---

# IQR

```text id="rev18"
Q3 - Q1
```

---

# Outliers

Extreme unusual values.

---

# Best Graph for Outliers

# Boxplot

---

# Practical 10 — Data Visualization III

# MAIN TOPICS

* Histograms
* Boxplots
* Feature analysis
* Outliers

---

# IMPORTANT THEORY

# Numerical Features

Numeric values.

Example:

```text id="rev19"
5.1
3.5
```

---

# Nominal Features

Categorical labels.

Example:

```text id="rev20"
setosa
```

---

# Histogram

Frequency distribution.

---

# Boxplot

Distribution + outliers.

---

# Outlier Formula

```text id="rev21"
Q1 - 1.5×IQR
Q3 + 1.5×IQR
```

---

# Petal Features

Best for separating iris species.

